properties.Title: Severe Thunderstorm Watch In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: This evening, conditions will be favourable for the development of dangerous thunderstorms capable of producing very strong wind gusts and heavy downpours. Do not forget that severe thunderstorms can produce tornadoes. Boaters could be surprised by strong wind gusts over bodies of water. ### Very strong wind gusts can damage buildings, down trees and blow large vehicles off the road. Heavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Severe thunderstorm watches are issued when atmospheric conditions are favourable for the development of thunderstorms that could produce one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to QCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #QCStorm.
Expires: 2019-07-12T06:04:01-00:00

properties.Title: Severe Thunderstorm Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: At 9:24 p.m. CDT, Environment Canada meteorologists are tracking a dangerous thunderstorm capable of producing damaging wind gusts, nickel to ping pong ball size hail and heavy rain. This line of severe thunderstorms is located from 12 kilometres south of Manitou Falls to 15 kilometres east of Whitedog, moving east at 55 km/h. Wind gusts in excess of 110 km/h will be possible with these storms. Locations impacted include: Grassy Narrows, Blue Lake Provincial Park, Vermilion Bay, Jones, McIntosh, Quibell and Perrault Falls. ### Heavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Large hail can damage property and cause injury. Very strong wind gusts can damage buildings, down trees and blow large vehicles off the road.
